dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura run out (Raqibul Hasan) 31 (20b 0x4 3x6 32m) SR: 155

dismissalComment.html: run-out, short on middle, pulled away towards deep midwicket, gets to the fielder on the bounce, Raqibul fires in a strong throw to the striker's end as Chigumbura attempts the second, appears to be a direct hit from the deep, Mushfiqur's hands are extremely close to the stumps and it might just be that he's knocked the stumps down before the ball made contact, it's a close call but the third umpire gives it out. It was a direct hit but Mushfiqur was too close to the stumps as the ball made contact. However, the decision's been made and Bangladesh have won

batsmen.shot: off side drive on front foot

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura run out (Raqibul Hasan) 31 (20b 0x4 3x6 32m) SR: 155

commentPreTextItems.html: What can Chigumbura pull off from here on? He can't allow Rainsford any of the strike. Rasel, whom he's managed to smack around, has been given the ball.

commentTextItems.html: run-out, short on middle, pulled away towards deep midwicket, gets to the fielder on the bounce, Raqibul fires in a strong throw to the striker's end as Chigumbura attempts the second, appears to be a direct hit from the deep, Mushfiqur's hands are extremely close to the stumps and it might just be that he's knocked the stumps down before the ball made contact, it's a close call but the third umpire gives it out. It was a direct hit but Mushfiqur was too close to the stumps as the ball made contact. However, the decision's been made and Bangladesh have won

commentPostTextItems.html: Zimbabwe's fighting effort is in vain. Chigumbura had too much to do with too few wickets in hand and had the fielding display from the hosts - they let off Shakib twice - been better, we may well have had a closer result. However, they'll take pride in the manner in which they went about chasing the big score though they'll expect much more from the top order. Williams and Coventry played superbly but they were under pressure throughout and had to build their innings after Bangladesh had made inroads. It's a 2-0 lead for the visitors in the five-match series and Shakib, with a century and two wickets, remains the favourite to be named the Man of the Match. We'll get you the presentation details in a bit. Lovemore Banda, lovely name, is the host at the presentation.

Utseya: "We didn't bowl enough good balls in the morning and didn't vary our pace a lot. The middle order had a lot to do and we lost too many wickets early. We need to keep learning from our mistakes through we put in a much improved performance today."

Shakib: "We've been playing good cricket and hopefully we'll play just as well in the next game. Every time I come in to play, I keep getting better. Hope this continues. We need to improve in all three departments, but mainly fielding and bowling."

Shakib's also the Man of the Match. That's all we have from here, folks. Thanks for tuning in and sending us your comments. Until the next ODI on the 14th, a must-win game for the hosts, it's goodbye from all of us here at Cricinfo. Adios!

dismissalComment.html: run-out, tosses it up outside off, Mushfiqur slices it behind point and takes two easily but Shakib is intent to taking three and charges down the pitch but there's no response from his partner who is ball-watching, the throw gets to the keeper who rolls the ball down to the bowler, he takes off the bails to find the Bangladesh captain well short of his ground

dismissalComment.html: he's given him! Bowled on a length, appeared to pitch on leg and angle in towards middle, Vermeulen went for the sweep, missed and was struck in line with middle and off. The umpire raised his finger fairly quickly. Replays indicate the ball landed just marginally outside leg, a close call, that.

dismissalComment.html: bowled'im! Slower one on middle and off, Masakadza bends low to swing across the line in an attempt to clear midwicket, gets an inside edge straight into the stumps, the promising start has been laid to rest

dismissalText.commentary: Charles Coventry c Naeem Islam b Mahmudullah 61 (64b 2x4 3x6 82m) SR: 95.31

dismissalComment.html: another promising stand comes to an end, held back the length, dropped it short, Coventry had made his mind up, came down the track and pulled it hard, got more elevation than distance and Naeem at deep midwicket held his nerve to take that comfortably just inches inside the ropes

dismissalText.long: c Junaid Siddique b Nazmul Hossain
dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Junaid Siddique b Nazmul Hossain 8 (14b 1x4 0x6 22m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: he's gone now! The slower one coming from the back of the hand, low full toss outside off, just pushes it through the line without and lobs it straight to Junaid Siddique placed perfectly at extra cover

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c & b Enamul Haque jnr 9 (16b 0x4 0x6 19m) SR: 56.25

dismissalComment.html: tame dismissal, that! Short of a good length on middle and off, the ball appears to stop on him just a little, not much turn there, Taylor is already committed to pushing it through the line off the front foot, lobs it straight back to the bowler who completes a good catch moving to his right

dismissalText.long: c Mahmudullah b Enamul Haque jnr
dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c Mahmudullah b Enamul Haque jnr 75 (71b 6x4 0x6 76m) SR: 105.63

dismissalComment.html: Williams goes! Much slower through the air, varied his pace there and sucked him into the big shot with a tossed-up delivery, landed full on middle and leg, Willaims came down the track, was done in by the pace and lofted it really high, still he managed to time it reasonable well but not well enough as Mahmudullah ran a  couple of yards to his left at long-on to take a well-judged catch just inside the ropes

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri c & b Shakib Al Hasan 39 (51b 1x4 0x6 73m) SR: 76.47

dismissalComment.html: Shakib strikes! Fired it full on middle, Matsikenyeri struck it hard but straight back to the bowler, didn't get the desired elevation and Shakib reacted well to his right to pouch a sharp one

headshotImage.caption: Nazmul Hossain player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nazmul Hossain player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Mushfiqur Rahim b Nazmul Hossain
dismissalText.commentary: Prosper Utseya c Mushfiqur Rahim b Nazmul Hossain 4 (2b 1x4 0x6 2m) SR: 200

dismissalComment.html: gone! Those two boundaries provided just a momentary high, closer to the off stump and Utseya attempts an identical shot but doesn't get it past the keeper this time, straight to Mushfiqur who takes a low catch, the slide is on

headshotImage.longCaption: Raqibul Hasan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura run out (Raqibul Hasan) 31 (20b 0x4 3x6 32m) SR: 155

dismissalComment.html: run-out, short on middle, pulled away towards deep midwicket, gets to the fielder on the bounce, Raqibul fires in a strong throw to the striker's end as Chigumbura attempts the second, appears to be a direct hit from the deep, Mushfiqur's hands are extremely close to the stumps and it might just be that he's knocked the stumps down before the ball made contact, it's a close call but the third umpire gives it out. It was a direct hit but Mushfiqur was too close to the stumps as the ball made contact. However, the decision's been made and Bangladesh have won
